00057   IntDataSet (const std::vector<int> & ddata) {
00058     std::vector<int> tmp = std::vector<int> (ddata);
00059     sort( tmp.begin() , tmp.end() );
00060     data = canonical( tmp );
00061   }

00064   IntDataSet (const std::vector<int>::iterator & begin, const std::vector<int>::iterator & end) {
00065     std::vector<int> ddata(begin,end);

00067     sort( tmp.begin() , tmp.end() );
00068     data = canonical( tmp );
00069   }

00083   DataSet *set_intersect (const DataSet & b) const  {
00084     std::vector<int> res ;
00085     const std::vector<int>* bvec = ((const IntDataSet &) b).data;
00086     std::set_intersection(data->begin(), data->end(),bvec->begin(), bvec->end(),std::back_insert_iterator<std::vector<int> > (res));
00087     // trim
00088     std::vector<int> trimres = std::vector<int> (res);
00089     assert (trimres.size() == trimres.capacity());
00090     return new IntDataSet(canonical(trimres));
00091   }

00097     // trim
00098     std::vector<int> trimres =  std::vector<int> (res);
00099     assert (trimres.size() == trimres.capacity());
00100     return new IntDataSet(canonical(trimres));
00101   }
00103   DataSet *set_minus (const DataSet & b) const {

00107     // trim
